From b377786bb62e069a0e2a0f77492889e24ecad841 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: caption-reviewer-dev <dev@example.invalid>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 02:04:44 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add second-folder compare mode

Select a second directory and compare images + captions against the
primary folder, without requiring identical filenames.

Matching cascade (first hit wins, leftovers reported as only-here):
  1. filename stem
  2. exact file bytes (SHA-256) - catches pure renames
  3. perceptual dHash within a tunable Hamming tolerance - catches
     re-encoded / resized / reformatted images (needs Pillow; the
     first two tiers still work without it)

The B side is a read-only reference (image with boxes + caption).
Two bridges: Copy B->A loads B's caption into the editor as unsaved
changes, and a manual-match picker overrides the auto pairing per
image (remembered per compare-folder in localStorage).

Backend: compute_matches + /api/open-compare-folder, /api/compare-item,
/api/compare-clear, /media-b/<rel>. Frontend: compare bar + read-only
B pane wired into the existing list/canvas without touching the
single-doc editor engine.
